name: treatment of waste reinforced plasterboard, collection for final disposal | waste reinforced plasterboard | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/29907/documentation

The process represents the collection of 'waste reinforced plasterboard' for final disposal. The waste contains 0.85kg gypsum and 0.15kg cardboard, while its density is 1000 kg/m3. 

The activity starts when the building demolition activity is ready to be performed. Transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.

The activity includes energy for dismantling, particulate matter emissions from dismantling and handling, and final disposal of waste material.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste
